  "text": "The right external carotid artery was permanently ligated distally and mobilized as described [CITATION_1] . The PE-50 catheter with 12 clots was inserted into the right external carotid artery proximal to the ligation and advanced through the bifurcation into the proximal internal carotid artery. Ischemia was induced by injecting the 12 clots into the internal carotid artery over a 30seconds period with 50 mL of saline. After removing the catheter, ligating the proximal external carotid artery and closing the neck, rats were placed into a magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) scanner (Bruker Biospec, 2.35 T, Karlsruhe, Germany).",
